# MEMBER 5 — Memory Management (Paging + LRU)

---

## What to Say to Mam

> "Memory management in OS involves two key concepts:
>
> 1. PAGING with Address Translation:
>    Programs use logical names. OS converts them to physical locations.
>    Our PageTable maps operation names to CSV files — logical to physical.
>
> 2. LRU Page Replacement:
>    Physical RAM is limited — it can only hold a few pages.
>    When RAM is full and a new page is needed, OS evicts the
>    Least Recently Used page to disk.
>
> In our project:
>    RAM (limited) = LinkedHashMap with MAX_FRAMES = 5 accounts
>    Disk          = CSV files (user.csv stores all accounts)
>
> When a 6th account is accessed, LRU evicts the least recently used
> account from the cache to CSV. Accessing an evicted account triggers
> a PAGE FAULT — it is loaded back from CSV into the cache."

---

## Code to Show

**File: `src/system/PageTable.java` — Address Translation**
```java
// Logical name → Physical file (address translation)
table.put("deposit",    "user.csv");
table.put("login",      "auth.csv");
table.put("loan-house", "house_loans.csv");

public String getFileName(String operation) {
    return table.get(operation); // "deposit" → "user.csv"
}
// Program says "deposit" — PageTable says "user.csv"
// Just like: process uses virtual address, MMU returns physical address
```

**File: `src/system/BankDatabase.java` — LRU Frame + Page Fault**
```java
// Fixed frame limit = limited physical RAM
private static final int MAX_FRAMES = 5;

// LRU cache — accessOrder=true = every get() moves entry to MRU
private final LinkedHashMap<String, Account> frames =
    new LinkedHashMap<String, Account>(MAX_FRAMES, 0.75f, true) {

    protected boolean removeEldestEntry(Map.Entry<String, Account> eldest) {
        if (size() > MAX_FRAMES) {
            System.out.println("[PAGE-OUT] Evicting '" + eldest.getKey() + "' (LRU)");
            return true; // evict LRU account
        }
        return false;
    }
};

// Page Fault Handler
private Account pageIn(String name) {
    System.out.println("[PAGE FAULT] '" + name + "' not in frames → loading from disk...");
    // read from CSV (disk) → put into frames (RAM)
    frames.put(name, account); // may trigger LRU eviction
    System.out.println("[PAGE-IN] '" + name + "' loaded into frames.");
}
```

